In this paper the results obtained with four different regularization schemes were compared: 
RTR = I. Using the identity matrix is the most simple Tikhonov-regularization method, penalizing high values of the reconstructed conductivity changes. In the following this method will be abbreviated as ‘IM’.
RTR = N with N the neighbouring matrix defined as:
